value.value: This gene is involved in regulation of hemoglobin oxygen affinity.

Human BPGM wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7q33 and is approximately 33 kb in length. This allele, which encodes bisphosphoglycerate mutase protein, plays a role in the regulation of hemoglobin oxygenation. Loss of function mutations in the gene is associated with familial erythrocytosis 8.

Bisphosphoglycerate mutase (259 aa, ~30 kDa) is encoded by the human BPGM gene. This protein is involved in the release of 2,3-bisphosphoglycerate (2,3-BPG), which is an allosteric inhibitor for oxygen binding to hemoglobin.
